{{!< default}}

{{!-- Page header area --}}
{{#post}}
  {{#if feature_image}}
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="page-header__img lazyload" data-src="{{img_url feature_image}}">
      </div>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">{{title}}</h1>
    </div>
  {{else}}
    <h1 class="page-layout__title">{{title}}</h1>
  {{/if}}
{{/post}}

{{!-- The main content area on the About Us page --}}
<div class="wrapper container-fluid">
  <div class="row page-wrap">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3>History</h3>
      <p>
          Gazette is a magazine style theme, initially developed for the Ghost Bloggind Platform.
          Gazette is fully responsive, developed for with mobile first approach.
          Tested in most of the major browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Internet Explorer, Opera and Edge.
          Gazette was tested on every Ghost version starting from Ghost 0.9.x. and it's compatible
          with all those versions. We provide support for the theme, just contact us if you have any problems.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <img class="lazyload" data-src="https://unsplash.it/1500/1000?image=1073"
          src="https://unsplash.it/768/520?image=1073" alt="about {{blog.title}}"/>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <img class="lazyload" data-src="https://unsplash.it/1500/1000?image=856"
          src="https://unsplash.it/768/520?image=856" alt="about {{blog.title}}"/>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3>Recent</h3>
      <p>
          Gazette is a developer friendly theme, in fact all of our themes at Biron Themes are developed this way.
          We include all the necessary files and also instructions how to customize the theme.
          We used modern tools like Less for the styling and gulp as a task runner.
          In the documentation you will find detailed description how to use customize the theme,
          ex: Change main color, changing the default font and more. If you get stucj just contact us and we will help.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


